Description: Alt Data Provider -- Daily Counts of Factory Production from Tesla, Rivian, Lucid, and more.
Full Description: REALTIME PREDICTIVE INSIGHTS FOR HEDGE FUNDS: Simple answers to high-value questions. Investors seek fundamental insights into the companies they invest in. They can gain a competitive advantage by licensing proprietary information that only a limited number of funds can find and afford. To build these high-value datasets, we strategically place cameras/sensors to collect images/data of business activities that map to key company performance insights. We can process that data with AI (Computer Vision/Machine Learning) to generate unique insights into high-value questions for Hedge Funds and other asset managers.  Specifically, in our first two datasets we collect highly accurate and precise counts of every vehicle (Model Y or now Cybertruck) produced by Tesla at the GigaTexas factory and all four models (S, X, 3, and Y) vehicles produced at Fremont, CA. We license this data to hedge funds seeking an information advantage for trading equities.  Investors call this type of information Alternative Data or External Data because it's not published or directly sanctioned by the companies we observe. It is often built through innovative technology from unconventional sources. As we scale up, we expect to have numerous high-valued locations. We are hiring in several areas, DM me directly.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Hardware, Software

We knew that there were indicators other than credit card and loan payments that could be tracked to provide an assessment of creditworthiness. That’s where Hatch Credit comes in. Description: Market Network for Social Productivity
Full Description: What is MyPeople? We're a peer-to-peer marketplace for buying, selling, and exchanging unique services and experiences. Tell me more! Services can be anything from housekeeping or logo design to a video chat with a chef helping you perfect your favorite recipe. The goal is to connect people who need help with something to someone who is available to help them. What's the story behind it? MyPeople was an idea that came to our Founder & CEO, Melissa Strawn, while she was a struggling single mom in the Bay Area with two kids to support. A short-term disability left her unable to work and she dreamt up a creative way to get her needs met while still being a valuable contributor to the economy. Melissa and her husband now have five sons and need a community of help more than ever before! They utilize the services of many of the helpers on the site and still provide services of their own. Why is this so important to you? Glad you asked! Not everyone fits into the typical workplace model. Some people have disabilities, familial responsibilities, or lack access to skills or transportation to get to the jobs that will pay them what they need. And some people just want to call their own shots! We are building a trusted community of people who offer their unique skills, talents, and services so that we can see a world where all people can earn a living doing only what they love. This comes with the bonus of knowing that you are helping lighten the load of someone else.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
